%kckcolorfeature 'Calculates some miscellaneous features for a RGB image'
% This MatLab function was automatically generated by a converter (KhorosToMatLab) from the Khoros ckcolorfeature.pane file
%
% Parameters: 
% InputFile: i 'Input ', required: 'input object'
% MultiChoice: feature 'Feature', default: 2: 'which feature will be calculated'
%    Choices are:
%   1: 'Maximum Color Distance over Area'
%   2: 'Standard Deviation over Area'
%   3: 'Color Mean over Area'
%   4: 'Lightest Value'
%   5: 'Darkest Value'
%   6: 'Value Closest to'
% Integer: red 'R', default: 0: 'red value'
% Integer: green 'G', default: 0: 'green value'
% Integer: blue 'B', default: 0: 'blue value'
% Integer: width 'Window width', default: 3: 'width of the filter window'
% Integer: height 'Window height', default: 3: 'height of the filter window'
% OutputFile: o 'Output', required: 'output feature object'
%
% Example: o = kckcolorfeature(i, {'i','';'feature',2;'red',0;'green',0;'blue',0;'width',3;'height',3;'o',''})
%
% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% ckcolorfeature - Calculates some miscellaneous features for a RGB image
%
%  DESCRIPTION
% This kroutine processes the input object plane by plane (in the d and t directions) and extract some features from the planes that composes a RGB image (actually any 3-element color system is usable, but for hue-based the circularity is not considered). The feature is extracted over a rectangular
% area and can be assigned to each individual pixel on the output image or in areas the size of the window on the output image.
% For the features "Maximum Color Distance over Area" and "Standard Deviation over Area" there is a single output value, so the result is converted to a 1-element object.
%
%  
%
%  EXAMPLES
% All examples for the Toolbox Color are listed on the file $COLOR/Readme.html
%
%  "SEE ALSO"
%
